CREDIT DEFAULT PREDICTION: RE-IMPLEMENTATION & MODERNIZATION

PROJECT MOTIVATION
This project re-implements the methodology from the seminal 
2009 paper on credit default prediction using the Default 
of Credit Card Clients dataset.

The aim of this project is to reproduce the baseline results 
from the original study and Enhance the analysis with modern 
machine learning techniques. Beyond reproducing the study, 
this project includes some exploratory data analysis (EDA), 
data cleaning, and feature engineering. 

PROJECT STRUCTURE:

├── data/ # Cleaned & engineered datasets
│ ├── clean.csv
│ ├── clean_train.csv
│ ├── clean_test.csv
│ └── engineered.csv
│
├── preprocessing/ # EDA & data preparation
│ ├── data_exploration.ipynb
│ ├── data_cleaning.ipynb
│ ├── feature_engineering.ipynb
│ └── modeling_baselines.ipynb
│
├── models/ # Model implementation notebooks
│ ├── logistic_regression.ipynb
│ ├── decision_tree.ipynb
│ ├── random_forest.ipynb
│ ├── gradient_boost.ipynb
│ ├── knn.ipynb
│ ├── naive_bayesian.ipynb
│ ├── discriminant_analysis.ipynb
│
├── helpers/
│ └── lift.py # Custom evaluation metrics (e.g., lift chart)
│
├── research/ # Reference papers and resources
│ ├── DefaultCreditCardClients.pdf
│ ├── MACHINELEARNING_.pdf
│ └── FEATUREENGINEERING_.pdf
│
├── info.txt # Notes and misc. information
└── README.txt # This file


REFERENCES
Yeh, I.-C., & Lien, C.-H. (2009). "The comparisons of data mining 
techniques for the predictive accuracy of probability of default 
of credit card clients." Expert Systems with Applications.

Dataset: UCI Repository — Default of Credit Card Clients
